To reveal the high cyclic and rate capability of FePS3@MXene electrode, the sodium storage mechanism was studied by analyzing CV profiles at diversity scan speeds from 0.1 to 1.5 mV s−1 in Fig. 6a. The overall charge storage mechanism of the FePS3@MXene electrode can be quantified by dividing the i (current) response at a constant V (potential) into two mechanisms: k1v (capacitive effects) and k2v1/2 (diffusion processes).i(v)=avb=k1v+k2v1/2.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
